The energy generated by the lightbulb cannot power the solar cells that light it.  Solar cells do not generate a fixed amount of energy.  They generate based on the energy of the light coming in on them.  Current conventional solar cells are about 5% efficent (I think... anyone know better?).  That is, if you have 100 watts of energy incident upon one, it would generate 5 watts of energy.  If you have a 100 Watt light bulb, the most energy you can get out of solar cells surrounding it would be less than 5 watts or so.<br>
